<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="103" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d103">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 600.119/1643</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-08">
                                        <hi rend="italic">November 8, 1918</hi>.</date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 3.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3512. War Trade Board [from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName>]:</p>
                            <p>No. 1823. Referring to your 1438, Department’s 2140 [<hi rend="italic">2340</hi>], October 22, 2 p.m., and my 1741,
                                Embassy’s 3078, October 25, 12 noon.<note n="1" xml:id="d103fn1">The
                                    latter not printed.</note> I have to-day received the following
                                from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SAWS1">Admiral
                                    Sims</persName>.</p>
                            <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>The naval authorities concur in the exceptions made by the War
                                    Trade Board in its general policy and listed under the headings
                                        (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>), (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>), and
                                        (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>), paragraph 4, of cable No.
                                        1282,<note n="2" xml:id="d103fn2">
                                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_997">p.
                                            997</ref>.</note> together with the modification of item
                                        (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>) given in War Trade Board cable
                                    No. 1438 of October 28 [<hi rend="italic">22</hi>], 1918.</p>
                            </quote>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Laughlin</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>